    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-08T17:04:08+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T17:04:08+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T07:34:08Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T07:34:08Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough will linger inland over the west until a cold front sweeps across southern SA on Thursday. This front will push the inland trough into the far north, exiting the state early Friday. A cooler southwest to southerly flow will gradually moderate in the wake of the front as a strong high pressure system moves in from the west from Friday, establishing in the Bight on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-08T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Slight chance of a shower south of Streaky Bay, near zero chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds northwest to southwesterly 20 to 25 km/h tending south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the late afternoon then becoming light in the late evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers east of Ceduna, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the morning then tending south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 16 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:50am to 3:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 6 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower east of Ceduna, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 13 with daytime temperatures reaching around 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower. Winds southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h turning southerly 20 to 30 km/h during the day then decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Light winds becoming south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching around 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
